{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T21:52:12.733772232Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-ab35c795","body":"Add daemon-side forced backend cleanup before treating a cancelled daemon-owned run as resumable. `finish_cancelled_dispatch()` marks the snapshot failed and returns after the shutdown grace timeout without killing or pruning tracked backend process groups (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:3001-3073`), while the process backend only falls back to an in-process background reap after cancel timeout (`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1670-1680`, `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:2138-2147`). If a supervisor SIGKILLs the daemon in that window, the background reap dies with it, leaving `active-processes.json` and orphaned backend groups behind; later `run resume` from a Failed/Paused snapshot never executes the stale-backend cleanup path (`src/cli/run.rs:1952-1958`, `src/cli/run.rs:3269-3282`).","dedup_key":"71cbc3b272a2aab297a5e5f7f6ea5c916b866a361e6e535f3beab7ce3f065515","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411212718","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T21:52:12.746925535Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-cbc33ab7","body":"Stop swallowing `release_task_lease()` failures on daemon-aborted shutdown paths. After cancelled dispatch, the daemon ignores the result of lease cleanup (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1520-1522`, `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1556-1559`), and the final shutdown sweep only logs cleanup failures (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:3078-3094`). But `release_task_lease()` explicitly returns `LeaseCleanupPartialFailure` when it releases the writer lock yet cannot remove the worktree/lease or clear the task reference (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:3468-3510`). That reintroduces the contradictory durable state this bead is meant to block while the daemon exits as if cleanup succeeded.","dedup_key":"6c879cff85f5f2e7a638194a49c29addc8c39d38aea486c46359ba27800af092","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411212718","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
