{"sequence":52,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T22:35:53.360611116Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-928bcfa7","body":"Add a daemon-side repair path for interrupted cancellation handoffs that survive only as `run.json`. `prepare_cancelled_dispatch_handoff` eagerly flips the snapshot to Failed and removes `run.pid` before the grace wait ([src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:2894-2913]), but the only code that appends the missing `run_failed` journal event is `finalize_cancelled_dispatch_handoff`, which only runs if the same process survives to finish the grace path ([src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:2916-2980,3031-3098]). In the supervisor-SIGKILL case from the bead description, the daemon can die after persisting the handoff and before finalization, leaving a permanently incomplete journal for that run. Mirror the CLI signal path’s later repair hook (see [src/cli/run.rs:1972-2024,3213-3217]) so a later status/resume/reconcile pass can append the missing terminal event.","dedup_key":"4c40e0bf8cbe2f0d58283ef08ec9678fa1e032539766daa855429c63e7511708","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411212718","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":53,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T22:35:53.379876935Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-19c9e48a","body":"Stop discarding `release_task_lease` errors on the remaining daemon terminal paths. `release_task_lease` now returns `LeaseCleanupPartialFailure` when worktree/lease cleanup only partially succeeded ([src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:3565-3614]), but the daemon still ignores that result after aborted PR handling, PR-runtime failure, reconciliation failure, normal completion, and ordinary dispatch failure in both multi-repo and single-repo flows ([src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:941-946,972-977,1033-1056,1087-1088,1595-1600,1628-1635,1651-1652]). Those branches can still report a task as terminal and move on even though the durable lease/worktree state is contradictory. Propagate or quarantine those errors the same way the newly patched aborted/shutdown paths do.","dedup_key":"cb0eb7471fe19982bd8b2a3f2e46147c366fa6d4936a88edf4983cf65ff1a14b","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411212718","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
