{"sequence":88,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T23:19:15.419317885Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-e406e00a","body":"Propagate or persistently quarantine `AppError::LeaseCleanupPartialFailure` in the multi-repo daemon loop as well. The new fail-closed behavior only exists in the single-repo path (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1130-1139`), but `process_task_multi_repo()` still bubbles `release_task_lease()` failures up into `process_cycle_multi_repo()`, where the generic branch at `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:589-610` just logs and breaks the current cycle. On the next poll that repo is eligible again even though the prior task kept contradictory durable lease/worktree state, so GitHub/multi-repo daemon deployments still do not actually block on partial cleanup failures.","dedup_key":"478f3f28cd70bf9139925498acc1a582419ee5690fd99d959959b24398c7132b","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411212718","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
